  "text": "## Standing Orders & Direct Debits  \n**Q: Can I set up a standing order from my SmartSaver Account?**\nA: Yes. You can set up regular, fixed transfers to another account:\n- Frequency: Weekly, monthly, quarterly, annually\n- Amount: Any amount\n- Payee: Any person or business (provide their account details)  \n**Q: How do I set up a standing order?**\nA: Online (easiest):\n1. Log into online banking\n2. Click \"Standing Orders\"\n3. Add payee and details\n4. Confirm amount and frequency\n5. Standing order active  \nOr visit branch for staff assistance.  \n**Q: Can I cancel a standing order?**\nA: Yes, anytime with no notice period. Cancellation effective immediately. No fees for cancellation.  \n**Q: What is a Direct Debit?**\nA: Authorization for a company (like utility company) to withdraw money from your account. Different from standing order (they initiate withdrawals, not you).  \n**Q: How do I set up a Direct Debit?**\nA: When paying a company, request to \"set up Direct Debit.\" They'll provide a mandate form. You'll receive confirmation when active.  \n**Q: Am I protected if there's unauthorized Direct Debit?**\nA: Yes. Direct Debit Guarantee:\n- ✅ Refund within 10 business days\n- ✅ No questions asked\n- ✅ Full refund amount  \n---",
